cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is likely because the paper proposes a novel online learning/reading environment that incorporates innovative math-scaffolding methods. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely because the paper utilizes innovative joint embedding, formula evolution mining, and heterogeneous graph mining algorithms to recommend high quality Open Educational Resources (OERs) to help students better understand the math-content in the paper. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is likely because the paper addresses the problem of math-content understanding for cyberlearning and cyberreading, which involves retrieving relevant information to assist students in understanding complex math-content. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is likely because the paper discusses the growth of the scientific digital library and proposes a solution to help scholars/students better navigate and understand STEM literature. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible because the paper addresses a societal issue of improving STEM education and making it more accessible to students.
